# OSL Digital Securities (OSLDS) Exchange API v3 Documentation

The OSL Digital Securities (OSLDS) Exchange API v3 provides a clean JSON exchange interface for OSL Digital Securities exchange users.

Note: The base URL referred in this document (https://bct.host) is provided by the whitelabel operator. For example, https://trade-hk.osl.com is the base URL for the OSL Digital Securities (OSLDS) Exchange operator.

## Group Quickstart Catalog

### Authentication
* [API Key Creation](#reference/authentication/apikey) - Obtaining an API Key
* [Obtaining a Push Data Token](#reference/authentication/datatoken) - Obtaining a token to access push data services

### Account
* [Account](#reference/account/account) - Create account info of the API key owner
* [Sub Account](#reference/account/subaccountnew) - Create a sub account for a specified crypto currency

### Activity
* [Transaction List](#reference/activities/transactionlist) - list transactions of the API key owner

### Funding
* [Send](#reference/funds/send) - Send fund currencies
* [Receive](#reference/funds/receive) - Obtain an address for receiving funds
* [Receive Create](#reference/funds/receivecreate) - Create a new crypto address for receiving funds


### Order
* [Create/Replace Order](#reference/order/ordernew) - Create/place an order 
* [Order Status](#reference/order/orderinfo) - Order status and detail of an order
* [Order Status By OrderId](#reference/order/{orderId}) - Order status and detail of an order

### Streaming 
* [Public Events](#reference/streaming) - Public event like market tick, order, order book,
* [Private Events](#reference/streaming) - Account, Order status, Trade status, and user activities

## Group Quick Start
### Getting an API Key
In order to use the API, you must obtain an API key and secret. 

This can be done through the web site, or via the API.

####Via the Web
For you to do this, login to https://bct.host, and navigate to the Settings page from the top-right menu icon.  You will see the 'API' tab there and please click on it. 

If you try to create the API and secret for the first time, click 'Create' button on the API Keys page to generate a new API key pair.  If you have enabled two-factor security, you will need to enter a one-time-password (OTP) now.  Please copy down the API key and the secret to a safe place for future usage.  Note that the website will only show the API secret afterward.

If you forget/lost the API secret, you can click the 'Reset Secret' button to re-generate a new API secret.  Please note that old API secrets will be disabled automatically once the secret got reset.  All old secrets cannot be used with the API server.

You can enable the API key to allows/disable move funds and place orders.

If a single API key/secret is not enough for your usage, you can create multiple api key/secret if needed for different applications.

####Via the API

You can generate api key/secret pair using the [/api/3/apiKey](#reference/authentication/apikey) service.

You will need your username, password, and one-time-password (OTP) if two-factor security is enabled.

Note that api key/secret generated by the [/api/3/apiKey](#reference/authentication/apikey) service cannot place order by default.   You can change this settings via the Web. 


### Authenticate using Rest-Key and Rest-Sign
The API key and secret can be used to authenticate with BCG servers. This is achieved via the adding two HTTP headers: Rest-Key and Rest-Sign to each API call.

Rest-Key is your API key.

Rest-Sign is an HMAC hash constructed from your API secret, your API method path, your post data, and uses the SHA-512 algorithm.

* Note that api method path follow the pattern of "api/3/methodName/subMethodName". This is different from v2, which api method path is in the pattern of "methodName/subMethodName"

To test your Rest-Signs, use the following pseudocode:

```java
function hmac_512(msg, sec) {
    sec = Base64Decode(sec);
    result = hmac(msg, sec, sha512);
    return Base64Encode(result);
}

secret = "7pgj8Dm6";
message = "Test\0Message";

result = hmac_512(message, secret);
if (result == "69H45OZkKcmR9LOszbajUUPGkGT8IqasGPAWqW/1stGC2Mex2qhIB6aDbuoy7eGfMsaZiU8Y0lO3mQxlsWNPrw==")
    print("Success!");
else
    printf("Error: %s", result);
```    

#### Java / Groovy
```java

String sign(String base64Key, byte[] bytes) {
    Mac mac = Mac.getInstance("HmacSHA512");
    SecretKey secretKey = new SecretKeySpec(Base64.decode(base64Key.getBytes()), "HmacSHA512");
    mac.init(secretKey);
    mac.update(bytes);
    return Base64.encodeBytes(mac.doFinal()).trim();
}

def tonce = (new Date()).time*1000    
def postBody['tonce'] = tonce;
// put other parameters in postBody

String postBodyInJson = new Gson().toJson(postBody)
String path = 'api/3/receive'
String data = path + "\0" + postBodyInJson
String sign = sign(secret, data.getBytes())

```
#### Python

```python

import base64, hashlib, hmac, urllib2, time, urllib, json
base = 'https://bct.host/'


def post_request(key, secret, path, data):
    hmac_obj = hmac.new(secret, path + chr(0) + data, hashlib.sha512)
    hmac_sign = base64.b64encode(hmac_obj.digest())

    header = {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'User-Agent': 'bctv2 based client',
        'Rest-Key': key,
        'Rest-Sign': hmac_sign,
    }

    proxy = urllib2.ProxyHandler({'http': '127.0.0.1:8888'})
    opener = urllib2.build_opener(proxy)
    urllib2.install_opener(opener)

    request = urllib2.Request(base + path, data, header)
    response = urllib2.urlopen(request, data)
    return json.load(response)


def gen_tonce():
    return str(int(time.time() * 1e6))


class BCT:

    def __init__(self, key, secret):
        self.key = key
        self.secret = base64.b64decode(secret)

    def request(self, path, params={}):
        params = dict(params)
        params['tonce'] = gen_tonce()
        # data = urllib.urlencode(params)
        data = json.dumps(params)

        result = post_request(self.key, self.secret, path, data)
        if result['result'] == 'success':
            return result['data']
        else:
            raise Exception(result['result'])

x = BCT('<key>', '<secret>')
result = x.request('api/3/order/list')

```

#### CS
```cs
        string key = "";
        string secret = ""; 
        string path = "api/3/order/list";

        long unixTimestamp = (long)(DateTime.UtcNow.Subtract(new DateTime(1970, 1, 1))).TotalSeconds;
        long ts = unixTimestamp * 1000 * 1000;

        string command = "{\"nonce\":"+ts+",\"max\":\"100\"}";

        HMACSHA512 hmacsha512 = new HMACSHA512(Convert.FromBase64String(secret));
        string input= path + '\0' + command;
        MemoryStream stream = new MemoryStream(Encoding.ASCII.GetBytes(input));
        byte[] hashData = hmacsha512.ComputeHash(stream);
        string sign = Convert.ToBase64String(hashData);

        var request = System.Net.WebRequest.Create("https://bct.host/" + path) as System.Net.HttpWebRequest;

        request.KeepAlive = true;
        request.Method = "POST";

        request.ContentType = "application/json";
        request.Headers.Add("rest-key", key );
        request.Headers.Add("rest-sign", sign);


        byte[] byteArray = System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetBytes(command);
        using (var writer = request.GetRequestStream()){writer.Write(byteArray, 0, byteArray.Length);}

        string responseContent=null;
        using (var response = request.GetResponse() as System.Net.HttpWebResponse) {
            using (var reader = new System.IO.StreamReader(response.GetResponseStream())) {
                responseContent = reader.ReadToEnd();
                Console.WriteLine(responseContent);
            }
        }

```
#### PHP
```php
$key = '';
$secret = '';

$param['max'] = 100;
$param['tonce'] = time() * 1000 * 1000;

// generate the POST data string
$post_data = json_encode($param);

$prefix = $path ."\0";

// generate the extra headers
$headers = array(
    'Rest-Key: '.$key,
    'Rest-Sign: '.base64_encode(hash_hmac('sha512', $prefix.$post_data, base64_decode($secret), true)),
    'Content-Type: application/json'
);

```

## Group Supported currency and currency pair


## GET /currencyStatic
### Obtain supported currency and currency pair
This endpoint returns a list of supported currencies and currency pairs of the platform.

No Rest-Key and Rest-Sign in HTTP Header.

### e.g bct.host supported fiats
```java
USD, HKD, EUR, CAD, AUD, SGD, JPY, GBP, NZD
```
###  e.g. bct.host supported crypto currencies
```java
BTC, LTC, DOGE, STR, XRP
```
### e.g bct.host supported currency pairs
```java
BTCUSD,BTCHKD,BTCEUR,BTCCAD,BTCAUD,BTCSGD,BTCJPY,BTCGBP,BTCNZD,
LTCBTC,DOGEBTC,STRBTC,XRPBTC
```

