# Group Authentication 

## POST /apiKey
### Obtain an API Key
This service creates a new API Key, or resets the secret key on an existing API Key.

Unlike other requests, this request is not signed with an API key, rather the user's credentials are posted in the request.

##### Request Definition

| Fields        | Description| Example |
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer |
| username        | email address of the registered account |
| password  | password of the registered account |
| otp      | otp key if the user has OTP enabled |
| allowMoveFund | true if the api key allow to move fund |
| deviceId    | unique identifying string for the calling client/ device. Note that subsequent calls with the same deviceId will reset the secret key - so this cannot be shared across multiple devices. |

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| resultCode   | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. |
| apiKey       | Identifier for the api key, which identifies the user |
| apiSecret        | Secret key for the api key which is used to sign requests. This must be secured as it can be used to compromise the user's account |

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers
        
            Rest-Key: <Your-Rest-Key>
            Rest-Sign: <Your-Rest-Sign>
            
    + Body
        
            {
                "nonce":"1393225933584",
                "username":"username@yourdomain.com",
                "password":"yourpassword",
                "otp":"123312",
                "deviceId":"name and unique id of device",
                "allowMoveFund": true
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
                "apiKey":"e218acc3-7907-47b8-879c-302f0c1904bc",
                "apiSecret":"WcqucbLH7fNDK6LeQXI+Ian5cvhVC3kYOUD/Q8mWaEW3CMsjEeBgCA3qBZKF6YckwTkb04OA1nNuoJFqsffr+Q==",
                "resultCode":"OK",
                "timestamp":1393319666969
            }

## POST /apiKey/create

### only available to Master API Key
Create or update a api key for user. Only allow if the authorized api key is the master API key.  

* Whitelabel client can set site owner's api key as the "Master" API key
* If you are site owner of one of our whitelabel clients, you can request this feature from BCG.

##### Request Definition
| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer |
| userUuid      | user's uuid | 41da01ac-e011-4a20-b3af-37ee05a885e
| deviceId      | name of api key | e.g. apiKey1
| allowMoveFund | true if user can withdraw fiat or crypto |
| placeOrders   | true if user can trade | 

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| resultCode  | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. |
| userUuid    | user's uuid return by autoRegister | 41da01ac-e011-4a20-b3af-37ee05a885e
| apiKey      | Identifier for the api key, which identifies the user |
| apiSecret   | Secret key for the api key which is used to sign requests. This must be secured as it can be used to compromise the user's account |


+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "nonce":"1468377906313",
            "userUuid":"6b2038d1-7e2a-446f-b8a0-0be00c44ca66",
            "deviceId":"testbyme3",
            "allowMoveFund":true,
            "placeOrders":true
        }

## POST /dataToken
### Obtain an data token for access to data push services
Use this service to obtain a data token and uuid for access to data push services. Firebase is currently supported.

The token expires after 24 hours - client software should regularly check the validity of it's token, and use this service to obtain a fresh one when required.

##### Request Definition

| Fields        | Description| Example |
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer | 

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| resultCode   | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. |
| token      | data token  | |
| uuid        | user's uuid  | |

