# Group Account

## POST /account
### Get account information
The platform has 3 unique accounts for each user. 
- `Available_Balance` is updated with deposits, withdrawals and retail trades (if supported by the platform). 
- `Exchange_Available_Balance` is the balance available to be traded on the exchange (if supported by the platform). Funds must be moved from `Available_Balance`. 
- `Balance` is the sum of `Available_Balance` & `Exchange_Available_Balance`.

If userUuid is being specified in request, the client can get the user account information if the API key is master API key
* Whitelabel client can set site owner's api key as the "Master" API key
* If you are site owner of one of our whitelabel clients, you can request this feature from BCG.

##### Request Definition
| Fields        | Description| Example |
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer | 
| userUuid      | (for master api key only) user's uuid |

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| resultCode   | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. |
| data      | info result  | See Info Result |
| userUuid        | user's uuid  | |

Info Result

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| Created      | created date in format (yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss)  |  |
| Language        | user's prefered language  | e.g. en_US |
| Login   | username | |
| Trade_Fee | ordering fee | |
| Rights | list of access right | ["trade", "withdraw", "get_info" ] |
| Wallets | map of ccy and wallet | See Wallet |

Wallet
| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| Balance      | Sum of Available balance + Exchange Available balance (Amount) |  |
| Available_Balance        | Primary account's available balance (Amount) |
| Primary_Available_Balance        | primary available balance(Amount) |
| Exchange_Available_Balance        | Exchange account's available balance (Amount) |

Amount
| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| displayShort  | Display in short | 199.99 BTC |
| valueInt      | Value in Integer | 19999400000 | 
| currency      | currency  | BTC | 
| display       | display in full | 199.99400000 BTC |
| value         | value | 199.99400000 |

+ Response 200 (application/json)

## POST /subaccount/new
### Create a new sub-account to receive crypto funds for the given token
Use this endpoint to create a new sub-account. There will be a new crypto address tied to this sub-account to recieve crypto funds.

##### Request Definition

| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer |
| ccy         | traded currency (currently one of BTC, LTC, DOGE, XRP and STR) |
| customRef | an alias of this subaccount, like "Entertainment Funds" (NOTE: please do not name your subaccount as "DEFAULT" or "default", these two key words are reserved.) |

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| resultCode   | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. | OK
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| subAccount  | UUID of the subAccount newly created.  |


+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers
    
            Rest-Key: <Your-Rest-Key>
            Rest-Sign: <Your-Rest-Sign>
        
    + Body
    
            {
                "nonce":"1393225933579",
                "ccy":"DOGE",
                "customRef":"Entertainment Funds"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
        
            {
               "resultCode": "OK",
               "timestamp": 1401332162768,
               "subAccount": "672ee29e-0a8b-4fce-b9d5-97b9cf278742"
            }



# Group Activities
## POST /transaction/list
By querying this endpoint, you can get your transactions (max result: 200). You can specify date range and/or offset so that you can paginate the transactions returned.

##### Request Definition
| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer | 
| ccy           | currency | BTC (optional)
| transactionState        | TransactionState   | e.g.PROCESSED (optional)
| from          | start time(inclusive) of queries transaction, format should be a number (UNIX timestamp in milliseconds) (optional)  | 1464675012000
| to            | end time(inclusive) of queries transaction, format is same as 'from' (optional)  | 1464679012000
| max           | Max results you want the endpoint to return. Note that it can be no greater than 200. Default value is 50 if not provided. (optional) | 50
| offset        | if there is more than 'max' results between the date range you specified, this field is useful for you to get the next 'max' results  (optional) | if max is 200, and there are actually 407 results in the date range, offset=400 will get you the last 7 results
| lang          | displayTitle and displayDescription for each transaction returned will be in the language specified. Default is "en-US". (optional)  | en-US


##### TransactionState

| Fields        | Description
| ------------- |-------------|---------
|SUBMITTED| Transaction submitted
|PROCESSED| Transaction has been processed
|SUSPENDED| Transaction has been suspended 
|REVERSED | Reversed 
|LIMIT_OVERRIDE_APPROVED | Limit overrided
|CANCELLED_INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS| Cancelled insufficent funds
|CANCELLED_LIMIT_BREACH | Cancelled - limit breach 
|PENDING_CONFIRM | Pending confirmation
|PENDING_SUFFICIENT_CONFIRMATIONS | Pending confirmation
|PENDING_REVERSE | Pending to reverese
|PENDING_LIMIT_APPROVAL | Pending limit approval

##### Language
| Fields        | Description
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| zh-CN | Simplified Chinese
| zh-HK | Traditional Chinese
| pt-BR | 
| en-US | English (US)
| ja-JP | Japanese 


##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| resultCode   | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. |
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| transactions        | list of transactions.  See Transaction  |
| count        | number of transactions returned  |

##### Transaction

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| transactionClas | FILL, COUPON and etc | 
| uuid| uuid of the transaction|  6d568392-ce9f-42b9-bfe6-074cffa78d6b
| userUuid | uuid belong to the user | 67271c1d -2f9b-48e2- a5bb-01c8a8ce11a4
| amount | total amount of the transaction| e.g -1.00345678
| fee | fee included in the transaction |  0.0
| balanceBefore| balance before the transaction |  105337.05233524
| balanceAfter | balance after the transaction |  105336.04887846,
| ccy | account currency | BTC
|transactionState | transaction state | e.g. PROCESSED
|transactionType | transaction tpe | FILL_DEBIT
|received | recieved timestamp | 1431004151000
|processed | processed timestamp | 1431004151000
|timestampMillis | created timestamp | 1464677126478
|displayTitle | Order Fill |
|displayDescription | Sell BTC @ 3231.23333 HKD / BTC or quoteId: xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxx|


+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
                "transactions": [{
                    "transactionClass": "FILL",
                    "uuid": "6d568392-ce9f-42b9-bfe6-074cffa78d6b",
                    "userUuid": "67271c1d -2f9b-48e2- a5bb-01c8a8ce11a4",
