Do not set offset and max for all orders


##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Possible values
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| resultCode | see result code| 
| orders| list of orders (see Order) | 
| count | number of orders returned 


##### Order

| Fields        | Description|  Possible values
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| orderId  | Unique id of this order. | 
| timestamp  | unix timestamp | 
| orderType  | IMMEDIATE_OR_CANCEL, LIMIT, MARKET|
| orderStatus  | Status code of this order | ACTIVE
| settlementCurrency  | Settlement currency | All fiat (HKD, USD, etc) or Crypto (BTC)
| settlementCurrencyAmount  | Settlement currency amount | null / numeric 
| settlementCurrencyAmountOutstanding  | Settlement currency amount outstanding| null / numeric 
| tradedCurrency  | Traded currency | BTC, LTC, DOGE, XRP and STR etc
| tradedCurrencyAmount  | Traded currency amount | null / numeric
| tradedCurrencyAmountOutstanding  | Traded currency amount outstanding | null / numeric
| buyTradedCurrency  | buying traded currency or settlement currency | true or false
| trades  | the list of Trade | 
| replaceExistingOrderId  | The order id that this order replaced | 
| limitPriceInSettlementCurrency  | price in settlement currency, do not specify this when placing a market order  | 



+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
