# Group Funds
## POST /send
### Send Crypto Coin
<br>This services allow support crypto send operations. The API Key must have "move funds" authority, which is configured on the web site.
<br>Send bitcoin/altcoin to a crypto-currency address.

<br>Please note that a confirmation email would be sent to you to confirm this withdrawal. 
<br>If you do not click the confirmation link on the email, the withdrawal will be reversed after 10 minutes. 
<br>If you would like this feature disabled on your account, you can visit our site and create a Fiat Express Withdrawal setting. 
<br>Fiat Express Withdrawal allows you to perform withdrawal without the need of 2-factor authentication or response to our email confirmation as soon as the total value of the transactions is smaller than the daily limit you defined. 
<br>The transactions are evaluated against your favourite settlement currency available in our site.
<br>Should you have any questions, please contact service@bct.host.

##### Request Definition

| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer |
| ccy        | currency (e.g. BTC, LTC, XRP) |
| address  | valid address in the selected ccy |
| otp      | otp key for security reason |
| amount      | amount to send (must be less than the available balance) |
| destinationTag| (This parameter only use for crypto currency with distinationTag such as Ripple)Destination tag facilitate identifying the purpose of payments and allow a single address to be utilized by multiple users. Additionally, these tags enable the return of payments. | 


##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| resultCode   | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. |
| transactionId       | internal transaction id of the transaction. *Note this is note the Bitcoin/crypto coin txid*. At the time this method is invoked, the blockchain TXID is not available. This identifier, however, can be used to match up the transaction updates send through the push data services. |


+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers
    
            Rest-Key: <Your-Rest-Key>
            Rest-Sign: <Your-Rest-Sign>
            
    + Body
    
            {
                "nonce":"1393225933584",
                "ccy":"BTC",
                "amount":"0.7653",
                "otp":"145212",
                "address":"113JFFCTt7MtqLi8BFS9TGqcxHqLqqttCH"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
                "resultCode":"OK",
                "timestamp":1393320170292,
                "transactionId":"81400064-a048-48d4-8f56-47a1484a5222"
            }

## POST /receive
### Obtain a current receive address for the given token
Use this service to obtain a valid address to recieve crypto funds.

##### Request Definition

| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer |
| ccy         | traded currency | e.g. BTC, LTC, ETH, XRP, BCH |
| subAccount | Optional. Uuid of the subAccount of which you want to get coin address. If not specified, this will be your default subAccount.|

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| resultCode   | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. |
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| address       | Valid crypto address | e.g. BTC, LTC, ETH, XRP, BCH |
| subAccount        | UUID of the subAccount of which the coin address is tied to |


+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers
    
            Rest-Key: <Your-Rest-Key>
            Rest-Sign: <Your-Rest-Sign>
        
    + Body
        
            {
                "nonce":"1393225933584",
                "ccy":"DOGE"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
               "address": "18PW33D6ci3VQNTDmuQLV8mo9embZ5jKW3",
               "resultCode": "OK",
               "subAccount": "550a1ae8-3867-4557-b40c-1a0434a65f95",
               "timestamp": 1401332352873
            }

## POST /receive/create
### Create a new receive address for the given token
Use this service to create a new address to recieve crypto funds.  New address will be created only the specified sub-account has received at least one account. Note that each account has a max number of sub-accounts, contact support to increase this limit.

##### Request Definition

| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer |
| ccy         | traded currency | e.g. BTC, LTC, ETH, XRP, BCH |
| subAccount | Optional. Uuid of subAccount for which you want to create a new coin address. If not specified, this will be your default subAccount. |

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| resultCode   | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. |
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| address       | Valid new crypto address | e.g. BTC, LTC, ETH, XRP, BCH  |
| subAccount    | UUID of the sub account that the coin address is tied to.  |

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers
    
            Rest-Key: <Your-Rest-Key>
            Rest-Sign: <Your-Rest-Sign>
        
    + Body
    
            {
                "nonce":"1393225933579",
                "ccy":"DOGE"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
               "address": "1NM2Jjy8sL6gKQx2uTmdzQpSxtRq8oKMT5",
               "resultCode": "OK",
               "subAccount": "550a1ae8-3867-4557-b40c-1a0434a65f95",
               "timestamp": 1401333876577
            }


## POST /transferfunds
### Move funds inbetween platform accounts 
Use this service to move funds inbetween different accounts that allows for trading.

##### Request Definition

| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce         | Ever increasing integer |
| from          | This is the move "From" account. Must be in CAPS |e.g. `AVAILABLE`, `EXCHANGE`  |
| to            | This is the move "To" account. Must be in CAPS | e.g. `EXCHANGE`, `AVAILABLE`  |
| amount        | This is the amount to move |
| ccy           | Currency selected to move currency | e.g. BTC, ETH, LTC, BCH, XRP, USD, AUD |

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| timestamp     | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| UUID          | Returns the transfer fund transaction uuid |
| status        | If transfer fund is successful, “OK” is returned |
| resultCode    | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. `INVALID_PARAMETERS` - Too many decimals or Exchange product not available`INSUFFICIENT_BALANCE` - account has insufficient funds to move|

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers
    
            Rest-Key: <Your-Rest-Key>
            Rest-Sign: <Your-Rest-Sign>
        
    + Body
        
            {
                "nonce":"${nonce}",
                "from":"EXCHANGE",
                "to":"AVAILABLE",
                "amount":"5.23",
                "ccy":"USD"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
              "uuid": "6a121bf0-6866-4a36-9244-81d155b62f21",
              "status": "OK"
            }
            
            // Wrong from/to, or too many decimal places
            // call when the platform does not support the EXCHANGE balance
            {
              "timestamp": "1575602536706",
              "resultCode": "INVALID_PARAMETERS"
            }
            
            // Account has insufficient balance
            {
              "timestamp": "1575602536706",
              "resultCode": "INSUFFICIENT_AVAILABLE_BALANCE"
            }

  
# Group Trading
## POST /order/new
### Create/Replace an order

By using this method, you can create an order with different order type. In addition, you can replace an existing order by providing additional parameters

* tradedCurrencyAmount and settlementCurrencyAmount is mutually exclusive. You can only specify one

##### Request Definition (Create new order)

| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce    | Ever increasing integer |
| tonce    | Ever increasing integer |
| order | see Order |

###### Order

| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| orderType  | Order type | LIMIT / MARKET |
| tradedCurrency  | Traded currency | BTC, LTC, DOGE, XRP and STR etc|
| tradedCurrencyAmount  | traded currency amount, numeric number with at most 8 decimal places | 1234.12345678|
| settlementCurrency  | Settlement currency | All fiat (HKD, USD, etc) or Crypto (BTC)
| settlementCurrencyAmount  | settlement currency amount, numeric number with at most 8 decimal places | 1234.12345678|
| buyTradedCurrency  | buying traded currency or settlement currency | true or false
| limitPriceInSettlementCurrency  | price in settlement currency, do not specify this when placing a market order  | 3000.12345
| immediateOrCancel | must be true for IMMEDIATE_OR_CANCEL orders. If false or not provided while order type is IMMEDIATE_OR_CANCEL, it would behave like LIMIT order. If set to true while order type is LIMIT/IMMEDIATE_OR_CANCEL, it would behave like IMMEDIATE_OR_CANCEL order. | true or false
| hiddenOrder | |
| fillOrKill | |
| replaceExistingOrderUuid | to replace existing order |
| replaceOnlyIfActive | Replace the order only if the order being replace is active |

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| orderId       | Unique id of this order. |
| timestamp     | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| resultCode    | Result code reflecting the success status of the operation. | 
| orderState    | Current order state | Including ACTIVE / PARTIAL_FILL / FULL_FILL / EXPIRED / PENDING_SUBMISSION. If order state is PENDING_SUBMISSION, it indicates that order is in doubtful state.  Need to do order enquiry to confirm the latest state.  | 

##### Possible Result code 

| Result Code      | Description
| ------------- |-------------
| ORDER_REQUEST_SUBMITTED       | Order request submitted. It is generally considered a successful response.
| INSUFFICIENT_AVAILABLE_BALANCE   | Insufficient available balance
| TOO_MANY_OPEN_ORDERS   | Too many open orders
| TOO_SMALL | Order value too small
| USER_NOT_VERIFIED | User is not verified for trading |
| INVALID_PARAMETERS  | Invalid parameters, including wrong currency pair, order amount/rate too big, too many decimal place, etc

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers
    
            Rest-Key: <Your-Rest-Key>
            Rest-Sign: <Your-Rest-Sign>
        
    + Body
    
            {
                "order": {
                    "orderType": "LIMIT",
                    "buyTradedCurrency": true,
                    "tradedCurrency": "BTC",
                    "settlementCurrency": "HKD",
                    "tradedCurrencyAmount": "1.01",
                    "limitPriceInSettlementCurrency": "3000"
                },
                "tonce": 1403076674170000
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
                "orderId": "eb7ebd89-0593-415e-b96b-d4d86cf35bb6",
                "timestamp": 1403076674228,
                "resultCode": "ORDER_REQUEST_SUBMITTED"
            }



## POST /order/info
### Getting Order status

* This method return order info of filled or active status.

##### Request Definition

| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| nonce    | Ever increasing integer |
| tonce    | Ever increasing integer |
| orderId  | Unique id of this order. | "565f2cdf-3f34-4881-bc80-46584c2c6b8d"

##### Response Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Possible values
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| resultCode | see result code| 
| timestamp   | UNIX timestamp in milliseconds |
| order| see Order |


##### Order

| Fields        | Description|  Possible values
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| orderId  | Unique id of this order. | 
| timestamp  | unix timestamp | 
| orderType  | LIMIT, MARKET|
| orderStatus  | Status code of this order | ACTIVE
| settlementCurrency  | Settlement currency | All fiat (HKD, USD, etc) or Crypto (BTC)
| settlementCurrencyAmount  | Settlement currency amount | null / numeric 
| settlementCurrencyAmountOutstanding  | Settlement currency amount outstanding| null / numeric 
| tradedCurrency  | Traded currency | BTC, LTC, DOGE, XRP and STR etc
| tradedCurrencyAmount  | Traded currency amount | null / numeric
| tradedCurrencyAmountOutstanding  | Traded currency amount outstanding | null / numeric
| buyTradedCurrency  | buying traded currency or settlement currency | true or false
| trades  | the list of Trade | 
| immediateOrCancel | true for IMMEDIATE_OR_CANCEL order. orderType should be LIMIT | true or false
| replaceExistingOrderId  | The order id that this order replaced | 
| limitPriceInSettlementCurrency  | price in settlement currency, do not specify this when placing a market order  | 


##### Trade

| Result Code      | Description
| ------------- |-------------
| tradeId | trade id
| orderId | order id 
| timestamp | unix timestamp | 
| tradedCurrencyFillAmount | fill amount
| settlementCurrencyFillAmount | fill amount
| settlementCurrencyFillAmountUnrounded | fill amount
| price | price
| ccyPair | trade pair | e.g. BTCJPY
| side | BUY or SELL |

##### Possible result code

| Result Code      | Description
| ------------- |-------------
