## Exchange Trades   public/trades/{market}/{ccyPair}
Get trade updates for a specific market(exchange) and currency pair

### Subscription

| Fields        | Description| Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| market         | exchange market  BCT
| ccyPair        | currency pair | BTCUSD (or any other supported currency pair, BTC as traded currency, USD as settlement currency)

### Event Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| event      | event type | exchangeTrade
| data      | see Exchange Trade | 

### Exchange Trade

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| uuid   |  Universally Unique IDentifier of the reported trade | 2d5df61a-3a77-46ee-8b8e-457a20f39b74USD 
| primary   | false if this trade is not primarily traded in {ccyPair}, true otherwise | false 
| tradedAmount   | amount of traded currency in this trade | 0.1 BTC
| settlementAmount   | amount of settlement currency in this trade | 55.250435 USD
| tradedCcy   | traded currency (currently it can be one of BTC, LTC, XRP and STR)| BTC 
| settlementCcy   | settlement currency (currently it can one of any supported FIAT currency, BTC, and LTC | USD 
| ccyPair   | currency pair, it should be the same as specified {ccyPair} | BTCUSD i
| price   | price of this trade | 552.50435 USD/BTC in below example
| side   | usually this is the side of incoming order | SELL
| timestampMillis   | unix timestamp in millisecond, time when this trade happens | 1399711468899 
| version   | 
| market   | market(exchange), it should be the same as specified {market} | BCT 

### Example JSON

```javascript
    {
      "event": "exchangeTrade",
      "data": [
        {
          "uuid": "2d5df61a-3a77-46ee-8b8e-457a20f39b74USD",
          "primary": false,
          "tradedAmount": 0.1,
          "settlementAmount": 55.250435,
          "tradedCcy": "BTC",
          "settlementCcy": "USD",
          "ccyPair": "BTCUSD",
          "price": 552.50435,
          "side": "SELL",
          "timestampMillis": 1399711468899,
          "version": 0,
          "market": "BCT"
        }
      ]
    }
```

## Private Events /private/{uuid}

Events specific to the logged in user.

This single topic subscription returns:

* Account balances updates
* Order status updates
* Order fills
* Activity events (notifications such authentication failures, order fill etc)

All private events have the "event" fields, this should be used to determine the type of event.

### Subscription

| Fields        | Description | Example
| ------------- |-------------|---------
| uuid | uuid which is used to access user-specific data from the push services. This may change with each new push token so do not store it for re-use (this is provided by a request to dataToken) | 

## Account balance update

Changes fairly requently - such as available balance changes when an order is placed.

### Event Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| event       | event type | "account"
| data | see Account|


### Account

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| balance   | total balance of {data.ccy} for this account | 
| availableBalance | available balance of {data.ccy} for this account
| timestampMillis | unix timestamp in millisecond
| user | user's uuid
| uuid | this account's uuid

### Example JSON


```javascript
    {
      "event": "account",
      "data": [
        {
          "balance": "4032.07",
          "availableBalance": "4032.07",
          "ccy": "CNY",
          "timestampMillis": "1399711469461",
          "user": "f51156d2-8416-11e3-ab68-525400098064",
          "uuid": "f5148924-8416-11e3-ab68-525400098064"
        }
      ]
    }
```

## Order status updates

Order states as the order moves through the state machine (lifecycle).

### Event Definition

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| event       | event type | order
| data | order. See Order| 



### Order
| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| uuid   | order's uuid
| orderState | state of this order. See Order State
| rate | quoted price of this order in {settlementCcy per tradeCcy}
| orderDateTime | time of creation of this order, denoted by unix timestamp in millisecond
| settlementCcy | settlement currency (currently it can be any supported FIAT currency, BTC, and LTC)
| tradedCcy | traded currency (currently it can be any one of BTC, LTC, DOGE, XRP and STR)
| side | BUY if this is a bid order (buy traded ccy), SELL if this is an ask order (sell traded ccy)
| tradedCcyTotalEstimate | fixed amount either in traded currency or in settelment currency. This is the same as {tradedAmount} if user specified fixed amount is in {tradeCcy}; or it is calculated by {fixedAmount} divided by {user specified limit price (rate)} and then round to feasible decimal places
| tradedAmount | total amount of traded currency
| tradedAmountOutstanding | amount of traded currency outstanding (not filled)
| user | user uuid which this order is belong to

### Order State

Enumeration of all order states possible

| State | Description
| ----- | ----------
| DRAFT | this order is newly created
| PENDING_SUBMISSION | this order is about to be active
| ACTIVE | this order is active
| EXPIRED | this order is expired
| PARTIAL_FILL | this order is partially filled
| FULL_FILL | this order is fully filled
| NO_FILL | mainly for Market order or Immediate Or Cancel order, this order is closed without any fills
| CANCEL_UNFUNDED | this order is cancelled due to the user's account doesn't have enough traded currency or settlement currency to fund this trade 
| USER_CANCEL | this order is canceled by user
| CANCELLED | this order is canceled
| SUSPENDED | this order is suspended
| USER_CANCEL_PARTIAL | this order is cancelled by user; and before the order was cancelled, it was partially filled
| CANCEL_TOO_SMALL | this order is cancelled when it's outstanding amount is below tradable minimum amount
| REPLACED | this order is replaced by another order 
| REPLACED_PARTIAL | this order is replaced by another order; and before the order was replaced, it was partially filled
| CANCELLED_REPLACE_FAILED | this order is not successfully replaced, due to replaceOnlyIfActive flag is set to true and the order is not active when replacing

### Example JSON

```javascript
    {
      "event": "order",
      "data": [
        {
          "uuid": "aa171fcc-3616-46ef-a722-cc0798d5e727",
          "orderState": "FULL_FILL",
          "rate": 3433.06521,
          "orderDateTime": 1399711468000,
          "settlementCcy": "CNY",
          "tradedCcy": "BTC",
          "side": "SELL",
          "tradedCcyTotalEstimate": 0.1,
          "tradedAmount": 0.1,
          "tradedAmountOutstanding": 0,
          "user": "f51156d2-8416-11e3-ab68-525400098064"
        }
      ]
    }
```

## Order fill transactions

A trade (fill transaction) occurred.

### Event Definition

Order states as the order moves through the state machine (lifecycle).

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| event       | event type | trade
| data | Trade data |

### Trade

| Fields        | Description|  Example
| ------------- |-------------| ---------
| uuid   | a Universally Unique IDentifier of this fill transaction (trade)
| order | to which parent order this fill transaction belongs, identified by the order's uuid (different from {uuid})
| tradedCcy | traded currency (currently it can be any one of BTC, LTC, DOGE, XRP and STR)
| settlementCcy | settlement currency (currently it can be any supported FIAT currency, BTC, and LTC)
| tradedAmount | amount of traded currency in this fill transaction
| settlementAmount | amount of settlement currency in this fill transaction
| side | BUY if this fill transaction belongs to a bid order (buy traded ccy), SELL if this fill transaction belongs to an ask order (sell traded ccy)
| price | price at which this fill transaction happens, denoted in {settlementCcy per tradeCcy}
| timestampMillis | unix timestamp in millisecond, time as of which this fill transaction happens
| orderOutstandingFixedAmount | amount outstanding unfilled out of total fixed amount of the parent order
| orderTotalFixedAmount | total fixed amount of the parent order 
| orderFixedAmountCcy | this indicates which currency the parent order's fixed amount is in
| orderTradedCcyExecutedAmount | executed amount in traded currency of the parent order as of {timestampMillis}
| orderSettlementCcyExecutedAmount | executed amount in settlement currency of the parent order as of {timestampMillis} 
| user | user's uuid

### Example JSON


```javascript
    {
      "event": "trade",
      "data": [
        {
          "uuid": "0a92baf5-6525-4e58-8def-afc929eb61b7",
          "order": "0558e23e-d143-4bc6-a354-0007887133cb",
          "tradedCcy": "BTC",
          "settlementCcy": "JPY",
          "tradedAmount": "0.01000000",
          "settlementAmount": "815.47",
          "side": "BUY",
          "price": "81546.52477",
          "timestampMillis": 1400208567305,
          "orderOutstandingFixedAmount": "0.00000000",
          "orderTotalFixedAmount": "0.01000000",
          "orderFixedAmountCcy": "BTC",
          "orderTradedCcyExecutedAmount": "0.01000000",
          "orderSettlementCcyExecutedAmount": "815.47",
          "user": "85c420e1-1f61-434f-a350-b5c294486cf1"
        }
      ]
    }
```
    
## Activity events

Many different types of user notifications are possible

### EventTypes:

|Event Types| Description |
|-----------|--------------|
| COIN_WITHDRAWAL| coin withdrawal
|   COIN_DEPOSIT| coin deposit
|    PASSWORD_CHANGE|
|    LOGIN|
|    LOGIN_FAILED|
|    ORDER_SUBMITTED|
|    ORDER_CANCELLED,
|    ORDER_FILLED|
|    ORDER_PARTIALLY_FILLED|
|    ORDER_COULD_NOT_FILL|
|    ORDER_CANCELLED_INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS|
|    ACCOUNT_LOCKED|
|    FIAT_WITHDRAWAL|
|    FIAT_DEPOSIT |
|    CASH_WITHDRAWAL|
|    CASH_DEPOSIT |
|    CASH_DEPOSIT_NOTIFICATION |
|    VERIFICATION_REQUEST|
|    USER_REGISTRATION|
|    USER_VERIFICATION|
|    VERIFY_TOO_MANY_TRIES|
|    TRANSACTION_REVERSAL|
|    DEPOSIT_NOTIFY_EXPIRE|
|    DEPOSIT_NOTIFY_SUBMITTED|
|    OTP_ENABLED|
|    OTP_DISABLED|
|    APIKEY_UPDATED|
|    APIKEY_PASSWORD_RESET|
|    APIKEY_CREATED|
|    COUPON_DEPOSIT|
|    CASH_DEPOSIT_SUSPENDED|
|    CASH_DEPOSIT_PENDING_FOR_FOUR_EYES|
|    PRICE_ALERT_NOTIFICATION|

### Example JSON

```javascript
    {
      "event": "userEvent",
      "data": [
        {
          "message": "Order has been filled",
          "eventType": "ORDER_FILLED",
          "user": "f51156d2-8416-11e3-ab68-525400098064",
          "ip": "",
          "timestampMillis": "1399713311966"
        }
      ]
    }
```
